    <p>CodeMie (Business Analyst)</p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>Prepared For</p></td>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>janpreetsingh_jolly@epam.com</p></td>
  </tr>
 </tbody>
</table>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h2><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-1.Introduction"></a>1. Introdu=
ction</h2>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-1.1Purpose"></a>1.1 Purpose</h=
3>
<p>This document outlines the functional requirements for the Online Librar=
y Management System. It describes what the system should do to meet stakeho=
lder needs.</p>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-1.2Scope"></a>1.2 Scope</h3>
<p>The system will manage library operations including book inventory, memb=
er management, borrowing/returning books, and basic reporting.</p>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h2><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-2.UserRoles"></a>2. User Roles=
</h2>
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
 <tbody>
  <tr>
   <th class=3D"confluenceTh">
    <p>Role</p></th>
   <th class=3D"confluenceTh">
    <p>Description</p></th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>Admin</p></td>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>Manages the entire system, users, and library inventory</p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>Librarian</p></td>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>Handles day-to-day operations like issuing and returning books</p></=
td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>Member</p></td>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>Library users who can browse and borrow books</p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>Guest</p></td>
   <td class=3D"confluenceTd">
    <p>Users who can only browse books</p></td>
  </tr>
 </tbody>
</table>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h2><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-3.FunctionalRequirements"></a>=
3. Functional Requirements</h2>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-3.1UserManagement"></a>3.1 Use=
r Management</h3>
<p><strong>FR-1.1: User Registration</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Admin to register new users (Librarians and Member=
s)</p>
<p><strong>FR-1.2: User Login</strong><br>
  The system shall allow users to login using email and password</p>
<p><strong>FR-1.3: Profile Update</strong><br>
  The system shall allow users to update their profile information</p>
<p><strong>FR-1.4: Password Reset</strong><br>
  The system shall allow users to reset forgotten passwords via email</p>
<p><strong>FR-1.5: User Account Management</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Admin to deactivate/activate user accounts</p>
<p><strong>FR-1.6: Guest Login</strong><br>
  The system shall allow guest users to login using name</p>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-3.2BookManagement"></a>3.2 Boo=
k Management</h3>
<p><strong>FR-2.1: Add New Books</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Admin/Librarian to add new books with the followin=
g details:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Title</li>
 <li>Author</li>
 <li>ISBN</li>
 <li>Category</li>
 <li>Publisher</li>
 <li>Publication Year</li>
 <li>Number of Copies</li>
 <li>Book Cover Image (optional)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>FR-2.2: Edit Book Details</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Admin/Librarian to edit book details</p>
<p><strong>FR-2.3: Delete Books</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Admin/Librarian to delete books from the system</p=
>
<p><strong>FR-2.4: Track Book Copies</strong><br>
  The system shall track available and borrowed copies of each book</p>
<p><strong>FR-2.5: Search Books</strong><br>
  The system shall allow users to search books by:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Title</li>
 <li>Author</li>
 <li>ISBN</li>
 <li>Category</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>FR-2.6: Display Book Availability</strong><br>
  The system shall display book availability status (Available/Borrowed)</p=
>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-3.3BorrowingandReturningBooks"=
></a>3.3 Borrowing and Returning Books</h3>
<p><strong>FR-3.1: Borrow Request</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Members to request to borrow available books</p>
<p><strong>FR-3.2: Issue Books</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Librarian to issue books to Members</p>
<p><strong>FR-3.3: Record Issue and Due Dates</strong><br>
  The system shall record the issue date and due date (14 days from issue)<=
/p>
<p><strong>FR-3.4: Borrowing Limit</strong><br>
  The system shall limit each Member to borrow maximum 5 books at a time</p=
>
<p><strong>FR-3.5: Process Returns</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Librarian to process book returns</p>
<p><strong>FR-3.6: Calculate Late Fees</strong><br>
  The system shall calculate late fees for overdue books at $1 per day</p>
<p><strong>FR-3.7: Due Date Reminders</strong><br>
  The system shall send email reminders 2 days before the due date</p>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-3.4ReservationSystem"></a>3.4 =
Reservation System</h3>
<p><strong>FR-4.1: Reserve Books</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Members to reserve books that are currently borrow=
ed</p>
<p><strong>FR-4.2: Availability Notification</strong><br>
  The system shall notify Members when their reserved book becomes availabl=
e</p>
<p><strong>FR-4.3: Reservation Hold Period</strong><br>
  The system shall hold reservations for 3 days before releasing to next in=
 queue</p>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-3.5MemberPortal"></a>3.5 Membe=
r Portal</h3>
<p><strong>FR-5.1: View Currently Borrowed Books</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Members to view their currently borrowed books</p>
<p><strong>FR-5.2: View Borrowing History</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Members to view their borrowing history</p>
<p><strong>FR-5.3: View Outstanding Fines</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Members to view outstanding fines</p>
<p><strong>FR-5.4: Renew Books</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Members to renew books (maximum 2 renewals per boo=
k)</p>
<p><strong>FR-5.5: Display Due Dates</strong><br>
  The system shall display due dates and overdue status</p>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-3.6ReportsandAnalytics"></a>3.=
6 Reports and Analytics</h3>
<p><strong>FR-6.1: Generate Reports</strong><br>
  The system shall generate reports for:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Most borrowed books</li>
 <li>Overdue books list</li>
 <li>Member borrowing statistics</li>
 <li>Books available/unavailable</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>FR-6.2: Export Reports</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Admin to export reports in PDF and Excel formats</=
p>
<p><strong>FR-6.3: Dashboard Metrics</strong><br>
  The system shall display dashboard with key metrics:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Total books</li>
 <li>Total members</li>
 <li>Books currently borrowed</li>
 <li>Overdue books count</li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-3.7PaymentManagement"></a>3.7 =
Payment Management</h3>
<p><strong>FR-7.1: View Fines</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Members to view outstanding fines</p>
<p><strong>FR-7.2: Record Payments</strong><br>
  The system shall allow Librarian to record fine payments</p>
<p><strong>FR-7.3: Payment History</strong><br>
  The system shall maintain payment history for each Member</p>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h3><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-3.8Notifications"></a>3.8 Noti=
fications</h3>
<p><strong>FR-8.1: Email Notifications</strong><br>
  The system shall send email notifications for:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Successful book issue</li>
 <li>Due date reminders</li>
 <li>Overdue notices</li>
 <li>Reserved book availability</li>
 <li>Account activation/deactivation</li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h2><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-4.BusinessRules"></a>4. Busine=
ss Rules</h2>
<p><strong>BR-1: Overdue Book Restriction</strong><br>
  A Member cannot borrow more books if they have overdue books</p>
<p><strong>BR-2: Fine Payment Requirement</strong><br>
  A Member must pay outstanding fines before borrowing new books</p>
<p><strong>BR-3: Renewal Restriction</strong><br>
  Books can only be renewed if no other Member has reserved them</p>
<p><strong>BR-4: Borrowing Period</strong><br>
  Maximum borrowing period is 14 days (can be extended via renewal)</p>
<p><strong>BR-5: Reservation Priority</strong><br>
  Reservations are processed on first-come, first-served basis</p>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h2><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-5.AcceptanceCriteriaSummary"><=
/a>5. Acceptance Criteria Summary</h2>
<div class=3D"panel" style=3D"background-color: #FFFFCE;border-color: #ccc;=
border-width: 1px;">
 <div class=3D"panelHeader" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom=
-color: #ccc;background-color: #E8E8E8;">
  <b>Acceptance Criteria</b>
 </div>
 <div class=3D"panelContent" style=3D"background-color: #FFFFCE;">
  <p>All user roles can successfully login and access their respective feat=
ures<br>
    Books can be added, edited, searched, and managed effectively<br>
    Borrowing and returning workflow functions correctly with proper valida=
tions<br>
    Notifications are sent at appropriate times<br>
    Reports generate accurate data<br>
    System prevents business rule violations</p>
 </div>
</div>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h2><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-6.FutureEnhancements"></a>6. F=
uture Enhancements</h2>
<div role=3D"region" aria-label=3D"Info" class=3D"confluence-information-ma=
cro  confluence-information-macro-information">
 <p class=3D"title conf-macro-render">Out of Scope for Version 1.0</p><span=
 role=3D"presentation" class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info-f=
illed confluence-information-macro-icon"></span>
 <div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
  <ul>
   <li>Mobile application</li>
   <li>Online payment integration</li>
   <li>Digital book lending (e-books)</li>
   <li>Community features (reviews, ratings)</li>
   <li>Integration with external library systems</li>
  </ul>
 </div>
</div>
<p>=E2=80=94</p>
<h2><a name=3D"OnlineLibraryRequirementsPage-7.ApprovalSignatures"></a>7. A=
pproval Signatures</h2>
